Updated Components EPS
Risk Reward for CVC Capital Partners plc (CVC.AS) has been updated

We refresh our earnings following 2Q25 fee- paying AUM statement. Despite the quarterly miss due to FX, we increase our 2025- 27 fee- paying AUM by \(\sim 1 - 2\%\) primarily driven by credit strategies. Our 2025- 27 revenues/net profit remain broadly unchanged with \(\leq 1\%\) change to forecasts. We reiterate our TP of €20 per shr.

Scaled private market play

Diversified capabilities geared to growth zones, with scope to scale across Credit, Infrastructure, and Secondaries Potential to benefit from increasing appetite for European exposure from end clients given investment skew at \(\sim 65\%\) European and \(\sim 80\%\) International Attractive blend with high proportion of stable management fee- related earnings driving strong operating margins, and gearing to recovery in carry fee and tariff de- escalation High- quality, loyal LP base with growth potential linked to cross- selling and extension into wealth Attractive entry point given share's relative underperformance YTD
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
Secular Growth: Positive View descriptions of Risk Rewards Themes here

In our bull case, larger success of fund size \((+30\%\) vs \(+20\%\) base case), higher MOIC assumptions (3.1- 3.3x for flagship PE funds vs target of 2.0- 3.0x) and a faster rate of realisations and deployments increase our 2026e earnings estimates. Our SoTP valuation applies a \(\sim 30x\) P/E multiple to 2026 Core Management earnings (adjusted for costs) and 2x P/E on 2026 carry.

Our base case assumes that full deployment occurs around 3- 4 years, fund life cycles of \(\sim 10\) years on average. Successor funds scale up by \(\sim 20\%\) vs. previous vintages. CVC offers attractive FP AUM growth supported by diversified capabilities and exposure to secular themes. Our SoTP valuation applies a \(\sim 27x\) P/E multiple to 2026 Core management earnings (adjusted for costs) and \(\sim 10x\) P/E on 2025 carry, which implies a blended P/E multiple of \(\sim 18.6x\)

Our bear case assumes prolonged macro uncertainty and higher- for- longer rates impact investor demand for Alts assets, leading to negative impacts and poor investment returns on funds. We assume longer fundraising periods along with weaker fund performance. We apply \(\sim 20x\) P/E to 2026e Core Management earnings (adjusted for costs) and \(\sim 8.5x\) P/E to 2026 performance fee earnings.

Overweight (O). The stock's total return is expected to exceed the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Equal-weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Underweight (U). The stock's total return is expected to be below the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.
